news.title: Indian rental housing searches grew 84.4% in Q2 2022: Magicbricks
news.para: Magicbricks.com is owned by Magicbricks Realty Services, which is a subsidiary of Times Internet.

news.title: SC seeks report on medical condition of ex-CMD of Amrapali Group
news.para: Advocate Manoj Singh, representing Sharma, said that the applicant is suffering from infection and his health "condition is deteriorating".

news.title: Income tax department raids Kanpur-based builder's house
news.para: The connection of Rakesh Yadav’s company with Ghanaram Infratech Company has come to the fore. The IT team is investigating the documents related to the company.

news.title: Pune: Properties with vermicompost pits increase 22% over five years
news.para: As per the property tax department of the PMC, property owners claiming property tax rebates for setting up vermicomposting pits on their premises stood at 31, 263 in 2017-18. This number shot up to 40,952 in 2022-23.

news.title: Over 2,100 sale deeds registered in Dholera till July 2022
news.para: In 2021, a record-breaking 2,484 sale deeds were registered netting the government Rs 11.39 crore in stamp duty and Rs 2.19 crore in registration fees.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation to set up construction & demolition waste processing unit
news.para: The civic body is looking for a suitable place, including one at Vellalore, to set up the unit at a cost of 2 crore, corporation commissioner M Prathap said.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to conduct property GIS survey
news.para: As HDMC is going through a huge cash crunch, corporators are pressing for a GIS survey to know the number of properties owned by the civic bodies along with the open sites, encroachment of properties and others and bring them under tax net to increase revenue.

news.title: Belagavi development body to start work on Kanabaragi layout in November
news.para: Due to legal complications, this project has been on hold for over a decade and a half. With the government's approval, the project will get underway soon.

news.title: Builders, property dealers protest against Punjab government over NOC rule for registry
news.para: Businessmen tried to get into the office of deputy commissioner along with the banners and black flags but they were not allowed to do so by the police.

news.title: Housing finance companies likely to grow at 10-12% in FY23: Report
news.para: The on-book portfolio of the Non-Banking Financial Companies-Housing Finance Companies (NBFC-HFC) sector grew to Rs 12.2 lakh crore as of March 31, 2022, registering 11 per cent year-on-year growth.

news.title: Gurugram: Four-member panel to probe into death of labourers after fall from crane
news.para: T​he committee will enquire into the causes behind the incident and fix the responsibility, propose safety measures to avoid such incidents expedite the process of compensation.

news.title: Delhi's LG directs DDA to convert leasehold properties to freehold within two months
news.para: DDA in its meeting chaired by LG VK Saxena, who is also Chairman, DDA, took major decisions that would make owning a house easier for the Economically Weaker Sections, promote green fuel in the city and ensure transparency in the allotment of land for religious purposes, amongst others.

news.title: Gurugram: Panel for structural audit of 18 societies finalised
news.para: Deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav said the panel members have been issued a letter of intent (LOI) and consultants will be assigned residential societies within three to four days.

news.title: Brookfield REITs declares Rs 171 crore dividend
news.para: The company said the distribution comprises Rs 82.1 crore or 2.45 per unit in the form of interest payment on shareholder loans and CCDs, and Rs 2 crore or 0.06 per unit in the form of dividend.

news.title: Police give NOC for demolition of Supertech twin towers
news.para: The Supreme Court's deadline for the demolition of the nearly 100-metre-tall illegal structures is August 28. The time from August 21 to 28 was kept as buffer period.
